Hypothesis

See bottow of this file for description of variables

Now read in data - there are 3 files (from different locations with different soils) We also read in climate data and link it to simulation results

# read in data files
resthin.deep = read.table("resthin.deep.txt", header=T)
resthin.shallow = read.table("resthin.shallow.txt", header=T)
resthin.mid = read.table("resthin.mid.txt", header=T)

# create aggregations by water year
resthin.deep.wy = resthinagg(resthin.deep)
## Warning: package 'bindrcpp' was built under R version 3.4.4
resthin.mid.wy = resthinagg(resthin.mid)
resthin.shallow.wy = resthinagg(resthin.shallow)

# add numeric representation for soil depth, shared, canopy
#comb.wy[1:10, ]
resthin.shallow.wy$soil <- 1
resthin.shallow.wy$shared <- as.numeric(resthin.shallow.wy$shared)
resthin.shallow.wy$canopy <- as.numeric(resthin.shallow.wy$canopy)

resthin.mid.wy$soil <- 2
resthin.mid.wy$shared <- as.numeric(resthin.mid.wy$shared)
resthin.mid.wy$canopy <- as.numeric(resthin.mid.wy$canopy)

resthin.deep.wy$soil <- 3
resthin.deep.wy$shared <- as.numeric(resthin.deep.wy$shared)
resthin.deep.wy$canopy <- as.numeric(resthin.deep.wy$canopy)

#View(resthin.deep$canopy)
#View(resthin.shallow.wy$canopy)

# put all three soil types into a single data set
comb.wy = rbind.data.frame(resthin.deep.wy, resthin.shallow.wy, resthin.mid.wy)
comb = rbind.data.frame(resthin.deep, resthin.shallow, resthin.mid)
comb = mutate(comb, drought=ifelse(wy %in% c(2012:2014),TRUE,FALSE))
comb$wyg = comb$scen-comb$wy

# if you want to isolate the change due to thinning substract results for 
# thin= 0.05 (the no thinning case)
tmp = comb.wy %>% subset(thin==0.05) %>% select(trans, psn, pcpool, thin, wy, wyg, shared, scen, soil, canopy)
tmp2 = left_join(comb.wy, tmp, by=c("wy","wyg","shared","scen", "soil", "canopy"), suffix=c("",".base"), fill=T)
comb.wy=tmp2
comb.wy = subset(comb.wy, !is.na(comb.wy$scen))



# subset and z-transform the controlled canopy data (1 is 'control')
comb.wy.ctrl.scaled <- subset(comb.wy, canopy==1)  
comb.wy.ctrl.scaled <- scale(comb.wy.ctrl.scaled)
ca <- comb.wy$canopy
comb.wy.scaled <- scale(comb.wy)
comb.wy.scaled$canopy <- ca
## Warning in comb.wy.scaled$canopy <- ca: Coercing LHS to a list
ca <- NULL
#
# write some of the aggregations to file for external use
#
#write.csv(comb, file = "comb.csv")
#write.csv(comb.wy, file = "comb.wy.csv") 
#write.csv(comb.wy.ctrl.scaled, file = "comb.wy-canopy-ctrl-scaled.csv") 
#write.csv(comb.wy.scaled, file = "comb.wy-scaled.csv")

#function needed for CFA Models
cfafn <- function(modelData, omodel) {
result<-lavaan(omodel, data=modelData, fixed.x=FALSE, missing="FIML");
summary(result, fit.measures=TRUE);
# Plot path diagram for this hypothesis::

semPaths(result, title = "False", curvePivot = TRUE, XKCD = TRUE) 

}

#HYP 1 Factor Analysis
model<-"
! regressions 
   trans ~ shared__trans*shared
   trans ~ pet__trans*pet
   trans ~ thin__trans*thin
   trans ~ wyg__trans*wyg
   trans ~ soil__trans*soil
   trans ~ pkswe__trans*pkswe
! residuals, variances and covariances
   thin ~~ VAR_thin*thin
   pet ~~ VAR_pet*pet
   shared ~~ VAR_shared*shared
   wyg ~~ VAR_wyg*wyg
   pkswe ~~ VAR_pkswe*pkswe
   soil ~~ VAR_soil*soil
   trans ~~ VAR_trans*trans
! observed means
   thin~1;
   pet~1;
   shared~1;
   wyg~1;
   pkswe~1;
   soil~1;
   trans~1;
";

cfafn(comb.wy.scaled, model)

# Some CFA/Path modeling using Lavann
library(lavaan);
modelData <- comb.wy.scaled;
 model<-"
! regressions 
   precip ~ pkswe__precip*pkswe
   tavg ~ pkswe__tavg*pkswe
! residuals, variances and covariances
   pkswe ~~ VAR_pkswe*pkswe
   tavg ~~ VAR_tavg*tavg
   precip ~~ VAR_precip*precip
! observed means
   pkswe~1;
   tavg~1;
   precip~1;
";
result<-lavaan(model, data=modelData, fixed.x=FALSE, missing="FIML");
## Error in lavData(data = data, group = group, cluster = cluster, ov.names = OV.NAMES, : lavaan ERROR: data object of class list
summary(result, fit.measures=TRUE);
